[2025-05-10T10:18:27.882Z] INCIDENT RESOLVED
  Service: payment-service
  Error: CORRUPT_CONFIG
  Root Cause: config.json was partially overwritten with the string `CHAOS_CORRUPT_JSON @@@` mid-file, making JSON.parse() throw SyntaxError on service startup. The payment processor could not read its database connection config.
  Fix: Restored config.json from payment-service/config.json.bak
  Test Written: /tests/payment-service/regression-2.test.ts
  Confidence: HIGH

[2025-05-10T10:31:55.119Z] INCIDENT RESOLVED
  Service: notification-service
  Error: LOGIC_ERROR
  Root Cause: helpers.ts had `status === 'active'` replaced with `status === 'inactive' /* CHAOS_LOGIC_ERROR */`, causing the notification dispatcher to skip all active users and only attempt to notify inactive ones — resulting in zero notifications sent and a silent failure loop.
  Fix: Restored src/helpers.ts from notification-service/src/helpers.ts.bak
  Test Written: /tests/notification-service/regression-3.test.ts
  Confidence: HIGH

[2025-05-10T10:44:12.003Z] INCIDENT RESOLVED
  Service: user-service
  Error: TYPE_MISMATCH
  Root Cause: The `port` field in src/index.ts was changed from numeric 3004 to the string "CHAOS_TYPE_MISMATCH_STRING". Express's listen() received a string instead of a number, causing the server to bind to an unexpected socket path instead of a TCP port, making the service unreachable.
  Fix: Restored src/index.ts from user-service/src/index.ts.bak
  Test Written: /tests/user-service/regression-4.test.ts
  Confidence: HIGH

[2025-05-10T10:52:38.774Z] INCIDENT RESOLVED
  Service: auth-service
  Error: MISSING_DEPENDENCY
  Root Cause: chaos-monkey removed `express` from package.json dependencies and prepended a broken import `import { nonExistentModule } from 'express-chaos-missing'` to src/index.ts. On next startup, Node module resolution failed immediately at the import stage.
